  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cameroon Train Crash - October 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A packed train derailed on the route that links Yaound&#xE9; and Douala on Friday 21 st October killing at least 60 people and injuring more than 600. Cameroon RC deployed 25 volunteers on the spot (3 local 12 from Yaound&#xE9; and 10 from Douala) and was the only humanitarian non-governmental actor on the ground in support to authorities search and rescue efforts. The IFRC is in the process of drafting a DREF to support Cameroon s Red Cross response operations. British Red Cross has received an unsolicited donation of 25 000 from GSK (GlaxoSmithKline is a British pharmaceutical company) which will be used to make a contribution to the IFRC DREF.</narrative>
  </description>
